      "side": 1,
      "message": "Unfortunately not.\nThe parser of the configuration uses a [string splitter](https://gerrit.googlesource.com/gerrit/+/refs/heads/master/java/com/google/gerrit/server/query/approval/ApprovalQueryBuilder.java#47) based on `_` character and it is expecting **exactly** [two tokens](https://gerrit.googlesource.com/gerrit/+/refs/heads/master/java/com/google/gerrit/server/query/approval/ApprovalQueryBuilder.java#168).\n\nSo we must have an `_`, and it has to be the only one.\n\nI think this could be made better bu just extracting **the last** token as the plugin name, without assuming there are only two of them. But this is outside the scope of this change.",
